HEADWORD: Greaves
<hw>Greaves</hw> <pr>(gr⟦emac⟧vz)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
dial. Sw. <ets>grevar</ets> greaves, LG. <ets>greven</ets>, G.
<ets>griebe</ets>, also AS. <ets>greofa</ets> pot. Cf.
<er>Gravy.</er>]</ety> <def>The sediment of melted tallow. It is made
into cakes for dogs' food. In Scotland it is called
<altname>cracklings</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>graves</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

